places.address: MFPH+FWQ Guru ki Maseet, Shri Hargobindpur, Punjab 143515

featured_reviews.review_id: Historical place..Guru ki Maseet, also known as Guru's Mosque, is a historical mosque that was constructed by sixth Sikh Guru, Guru Hargobind Sahib at request of local Muslims of Sri Hargobindpur . Situated in Sri Hargobindpur town on the banks of River Beas, it is recognized as a historic site by UNESCO.
featured_reviews.review_text: Historical place..Guru ki Maseet, also known as Guru's Mosque, is a historical mosque that was constructed by sixth Sikh Guru, Guru Hargobind Sahib at request of local Muslims of Sri Hargobindpur . Situated in Sri Hargobindpur town on the banks of River Beas, it is recognized as a historic site by UNESCO.

featured_reviews.review_id: This is a historical mosque build by Sri Guru Hargobind Sahib ji 6th Guru of Sikhs. This was built on demand by Muslims to be able to practice their religion. This place is looked after by the Nihangs at the moment. Currently it is used as a small Gurdwara, however some Muslim groups still come regularly to pray and eat langar made by the Nihang Singh. After partition Muslims asked the Sikhs to look after this building as they left the village. If a Muslim group is willing to look after this place with daily prays and maintaining the building, the Sikhs are willing to give the mosque back.
